<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-21840] camel-http does not encode path correctly when used with HTTP_QUERY header</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-21840</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During update from Camel 2.x to 4.x we found a bug in Camel-http. It no longer encodes Http path correctly when used with header HTTP_QUERY.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that HttpProducer does not convert the path to ASCIIString, since it uses the wrong variable when creating HttpUriRequest.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Camel 2.x:&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
http-outgoing-0 &amp;gt;&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;GET /&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;rest&lt;/span&gt;/service?ProcesName=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;Ans%C3%A6ttelse&apos;&lt;/span&gt; HTTP/1.1[\r][\n]&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Camel 4.x:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
http-outgoing-0 &amp;gt;&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;GET /&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;rest&lt;/span&gt;/service?ProcesName=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;Ans[0xffffffe6]ttelse&apos;&lt;/span&gt; HTTP/1.1[\r][\n]&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The problem was introduced in version 3.10.0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
